4.0 of 5 bubbles
Reliving history
Sep 2015 • Couples
Da Nang Museum of Cham Sculpture.
Strongly recommended as a place to visit in Da Nang and situated to the southern side of the downtown. Entrance fee is 20,000 Dong. The building in which the exhibits housed is itself worth visiting although maintenance could be improved. Inside the building there is no air conditioning so although the ceiling are high the building in the middle of the day tends to be hot and stuffy. That said the exhibits are well presented and the narrative more often than not is in English as well as Vietnamese. At various points around the museum there are laminated A4 cards explaining the background to the exhibits in that particularly part of the musuem.
There is a souvenir and gift shop before the exit. Allow around 1 hour for viewing the display.
