Phiphawin
Amphoe Muang Khon Kaen, Khon Kaen, Thailand251 contributions
Gigantic collection
Aug 2019 • Business
If you're into arts, cultures, and history, or if you just want a great location for your photo shooting, Da Nang Museum of Cham Sculpture is a highly recommended place to visit! The museum is located near the Dragon Bridge on the tail side and the entran fee is 60,000 VND each. It is closed at 5.30pm. The old light yellow building and surrounded beautiful trees can really comfort us.
The great collection simply make us stunned whennwe enter the exhibition sections. Descriptions and explanations are QR coded and 🎧 guided headsets are available as well.
Although the exhibition rooms and halls are rather warm, the displayed sculptures are truely amazing.
Da Nang has three close ancient cities which also include My Son where day tours can be arranged.
This museum is the largest Cham sculpture collection in the world. This 's another reason you shouldn't miss it and need at least 2 hours to appreciate and of course learn a lot of history here.
